Write a java program to take array length as input from user and create an integer array take 
element from user and store elements into the array Call a method printArray()present in 
PrintArray class which will print the array in forward direction and in reverse direction.

Note:Use each loop for printing in forward direction.


Explanation:
Asking the user to enter the length of an array.
calling a method printArray()in PrintArray class.
we have to create an int array.
Asking the user to enter the elements of the array.
Storing the elements in the array by using the for loop.
Displaying the elements of the array in forward direction using the Enhanced for loop.
Displaying the elements of the array in reverse direction using the for loop.
